  <!-- ── About Page ──────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <item>
    <title>About</title>
    <dc:creator>milo</dc:creator>
    <content:encoded><![CDATA[
<h2>Design-engineering, from first principles.</h2>

<p>I&rsquo;m Milo Arden &mdash; an independent designer and front-end engineer based in New York. I help founders turn rough product ideas into polished, fast, considered software &mdash; from first sketch to production.</p>

<p>Over the past seven years I&rsquo;ve worked across startups, research labs, and agencies. Every engagement starts with the same question: <em>what&rsquo;s the simplest thing that could actually work?</em></p>

<h3>How I work</h3>
<p>I operate as a small, senior team of one. Research, design, and engineering live under a single roof. That means less handoff, faster iteration, and software that feels cohesive from the inside out.</p>

<h3>Tools &amp; stack</h3>
<p>React, TypeScript, and Tailwind for most product work. Figma for design. Framer Motion or GSAP for motion. Comfortable across the stack, and will pick up whatever the team is already using.</p>

<blockquote>
<p>&ldquo;The best interfaces don&rsquo;t ask to be noticed. They hold the weight of the content they carry.&rdquo;</p>
</blockquote>

<h3>Values</h3>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Clarity over cleverness.</strong> Simple decisions compound into great products.</li>
  <li><strong>Ship early, refine often.</strong> Feedback is cheaper than speculation.</li>
  <li><strong>Accessibility is non-negotiable.</strong> Good design works for everyone.</li>
</ul>
]]></content:encoded>
